Noncommercial Purposes Only

Any noncommercial purpose is a permitted purpose. A commercial purpose
is any purpose primarily intended for or directed toward commercial
advantage or monetary compensation. Determining whether a purpose is
commercial or noncommercial depends primarily on the nature of the
activity, not the legal structure of the entity performing it. The
following are examples of noncommercial purposes:

- Personal use
- Academic research
- Education
- Open source software development
- Running the software for your own internal operations
- Evaluation and experimentation

The following are examples of commercial purposes that are not permitted:

- Providing the software, or services built on it, for a fee
- Incorporating the software into a commercial product or service
- Using the software to generate revenue, directly or indirectly

Notices

You must ensure that anyone who gets a copy of any part of the software
from you also gets a copy of these terms or the URL for them above, as
